# Implementation Plan - Granola Web (Copycat)

This plan outlines the steps to build a web-based "Granola" clone—a beautiful, local-first meeting notepad that records audio and uses AI to enhance notes.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Keys**: This application will require an OpenAI API key (or compatible) to perform Transcription (Whisper) and Summarization (GPT-4o/mini). I will build a "Settings" modal for you to input this key, which will be stored only in your browser's LocalStorage.

> [!NOTE]
> **Tech Stack**:
> - **Framework**: Next.js 14+ (App Router)
> - **Styling**: Vanilla CSS (CSS Modules & Variables) for a bespoke, premium "Granola" look.
> - **Storage**: IndexedDB (via `idb`) for local-first data storage (Privacy focused).
> - **Icons**: Lucide React.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Setup
- Initialize a new Next.js project at `/Users/canerden/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/granola-web`.
- Clean up default styles and implement a custom Design System in `globals.css` focusing on:
    - **Typography**: Inter (sans-serif) or similar clean font.
    - **Colors**: Warm off-whites, sharp blacks, and "grainy" textures if possible.
    - **Layout**: Flexbox/Grid based dashboard layout.

### Core Components ([NEW])
#### `components/Layout/Shell.js`
- Main application shell with a Sidebar (History) and Main Area (Editor).

#### `components/Editor/NoteEditor.js`
- A clean, distraction-free text area for typing notes during the meeting.

#### `components/Recorder/AudioRecorder.js`
- Uses `MediaRecorder` API to capture audio.
- Visual feedback (red dot, timer, potentially a waveform).

#### `lib/db.js`
- Utility to interact with IndexedDB to save:
    - Audio blobs (if size permits, or just metadata).
    - Note content.
    - Transcripts and AI summaries.

### AI Integration
#### `lib/ai.js`
- Functions to call OpenAI API.
- `transcribeAudio(blob)`: Sends audio to Whisper.
- `generateSummary(transcript, userNotes)`: Sends text to LLM to merge and format.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- None planned for this MVP phase.

### Manual Verification
1. **Recording Test**: Click Record, talk, Stop. Verify audio plays back.
2. **Note Taking**: Type notes while "recording".
3. **Enhancement Flow**:
    - Input a dummy API key (or real one).
    - Trigger "Enhance".
    - Verify that "Simulated" or Real response updates the note view.
4. **Persistence**: Reload page, ensure past meeting is still in the sidebar.
